Subject: RE: [T2] POR-15 & fiberglass

Somebody else on this list said to use Penetrol. I have ordered it and it
just came in yesterday. I have not had a chance to use it, but will in the
next few weeks. The website says that it restores luster to faded
fiberglass. It is used on boats, so I think it will do the job. For
cleaning, I clean mine with Simple Green and a brush. It does a great job
except for some black stuff on the side. I am going to try goo gone on that.
The Penetrol was $9.00 a quart from
http://www.jamestowndistributors.com/cgi-local/SoftCart.exe/store/product_pa
ges/SOLPNQ.html?L+scstore+zwzd6404ffb883b8+1025341187.

You may be able to find it cheaper, locally. 

Corbett

